            "title": "Kaisertum und Kalifat : der imperiale Monotheismus im Fr\u00fch- und Hochmittelalter",
            "abstract": [
                "The historical differences between Europe and the Near East in the Middle Ages have often been described with catchwords: \"separation of church and state\" in the West; \"merging of politics and religion\" in Byzantium and Islam. H\u00f6fert opposes this outdated idea, and instead is concerned with the question of how the modern concept of religion can be applied to pre-modern circumstances. Her central thesis is that the Roman-Byzantine Empire, the Umayyad and Abbasid Empires, along with Carolingian and Ottonian rule and the papacy, all contributed to the Late Antique conception of religion and politics as imperial monotheism, but all developed this idea in different and contentious ways",
                "Das K\u00f6nigtum und die transkulturelle Perspektive -- Analytische Hauptkategorien und Vorgehensweise der Untersuchung -- Die Ausgangslage im r\u00f6mischen Kaiserreich bis zu Konstantin I -- Die christliche Universalmonarchie im r\u00f6misch-byzantinischen Reich -- Die muslimische Universalmonarchie im umaiyadischen und abbasidischen Reich -- Das lateinische Kaisertum -- Schlussfolgerung"
            ],
